1. Nisam mogao da završim trku, pa sam *odustao* u drugom krugu. (I couldn't finish the race, so I *gave up* in the second lap.)
2. On je *odustao* od ideje da kupi novi automobil jer mu je stara mašina još uvek dobra. (He *abandoned* the idea of buying a new car because his old machine is still good.)
3. Nikada nemoj *odustati* od svojih snova, ma koliko god teško bilo. (Never *give up* on your dreams, no matter how hard it may be.)
4. Kada smo videli da se stanje neće popraviti, odlučili smo da *odustanemo* od posla. (When we saw that the situation wouldn't improve, we decided to *give up* on the job.)
5. Mnogi ljudi *odustaju* od učenja stranog jezika jer im se čini da je preteško. (Many people *give up* on learning a foreign language because they think it's too difficult.)
6. Iako je bio iscrpljen, nije *odustao* od trke i na kraju je pobedio. (Although he was exhausted, he didn't *give up* on the race and ultimately won.)
7. Kada je shvatio da je napravio grešku, brzo se vratio na početak i nije *odustao* od pokušaja. (When he realized he made a mistake, he quickly went back to the beginning and didn't *give up* on trying.)
8. *Odustajanje* nije opcija ako želimo da uspemo u životu. (Giving up is not an option if we want to succeed in life.)
9. Mnogi sportisti *odustaju* od takmičenja zbog povreda. (Many athletes *withdraw* from competitions due to injuries.)
10. Moramo *odustati* od ideje da možemo da rešimo sve probleme sami i potražiti pomoć. (We have to *abandon* the idea that we can solve all problems on our own and seek help.)